---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro';
---

<ProjectLayout
  title="StreamForge"
  subtitle="Distributed Event Processing Pipeline"
  description="A distributed event processing pipeline built with Go that processes high-volume events with worker pools, batch writes, and fault tolerance."
  github="https://github.com/carissaayo/go-distributed-event-processing"
  tags={['Go', 'MongoDB', 'Prometheus', 'Chi', 'Zap']}
>
  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-4">Overview</h2>
    <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      StreamForge is a distributed event processing pipeline that receives events via HTTP,
      queues them in a buffered channel, and processes them concurrently with a pool of worker
      goroutines. Processed events are batch-written to MongoDB. The system includes structured
      logging, Prometheus metrics, health checks, and graceful shutdown.
    </p>
    <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
      This project demonstrates core Go concurrency patterns applied to a real infrastructure
      problem: how to ingest, route, and persist high-volume events reliably without losing data
      or blocking callers.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-6">Architecture</h2>
    <div class="architecture-block">
      <pre><code>Client
  │
  ▼
HTTP API (Chi Router)
  │
  ▼
Event Validation & Enrichment
  │
  ▼
Buffered Channel (10,000 capacity)
  │
  ▼
Event Router (routes by event type)
  │
  ├──── Worker 0 ───┐
  ├──── Worker 1 ───┤
  ├──── Worker 2 ───┤
  ├──── ...         ├──→ Batch Writer (flushes every 100 events or 1s)
  ├──── Worker 6 ───┤                     │
  └──── Worker 7 ───┘                     ▼
                                       MongoDB
                                          │
                                    (on failure)
                                          ▼
                                  Dead Letter Queue</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-4">How It Works</h2>
    <ol class="space-y-3 text-zinc-400">
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="text-cyan-400 font-mono text-sm shrink-0">01</span>
        <span>HTTP handler validates and enriches the incoming event (timestamps, metadata)</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="text-cyan-400 font-mono text-sm shrink-0">02</span>
        <span>Event is submitted to a buffered channel using non-blocking send. Returns 503 if the buffer is full (backpressure).</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="text-cyan-400 font-mono text-sm shrink-0">03</span>
        <span>One of 8 worker goroutines picks up the event from the shared channel</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="text-cyan-400 font-mono text-sm shrink-0">04</span>
        <span>The event router directs it to the appropriate processor based on event type</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="text-cyan-400 font-mono text-sm shrink-0">05</span>
        <span>The processor adds the event to a batch buffer protected by a mutex</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="text-cyan-400 font-mono text-sm shrink-0">06</span>
        <span>The batcher flushes to MongoDB when the buffer hits 100 events or every 1 second (whichever comes first)</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="text-cyan-400 font-mono text-sm shrink-0">07</span>
        <span>Failed writes go to an in-memory dead letter queue for later inspection</span>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-6">Key Engineering Decisions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-8">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mb-2">Worker Pool Pattern</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          A fixed number of goroutines read from a shared buffered channel. This decouples HTTP
          handlers from event processing, provides natural backpressure when the buffer fills,
          and bounds the concurrency to prevent resource exhaustion. The worker count is
          configurable via environment variables.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mb-2">Non-blocking Submit with Backpressure</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          The <code class="text-cyan-400 font-mono text-sm">select</code> statement with a
          <code class="text-cyan-400 font-mono text-sm">default</code> case prevents the HTTP handler
          from blocking when the channel is full. Instead, it returns a 503 Service Unavailable,
          giving clients a clear signal to retry. This is preferable to unbounded queuing which
          hides backpressure and risks OOM.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mb-2">Batch Writes with Time + Size Triggers</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          Events are accumulated in a buffer and flushed to MongoDB either when the batch reaches
          100 events or after 1 second, whichever comes first. This amortizes the per-write cost
          while maintaining acceptable latency. The batcher uses a <code class="text-cyan-400 font-mono text-sm">sync.Mutex</code>
          to protect the shared buffer across goroutines.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mb-2">Graceful Shutdown</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          On SIGINT/SIGTERM, the system stops accepting new events, drains the buffered channel,
          waits for workers to finish via <code class="text-cyan-400 font-mono text-sm">sync.WaitGroup</code>,
          performs a final flush of the batch buffer, and cleanly disconnects from MongoDB. No
          events are lost during shutdown.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-6">Go Patterns Used</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <th class="text-left py-3 pr-6 text-zinc-400 font-mono font-normal">Pattern</th>
            <th class="text-left py-3 text-zinc-400 font-mono font-normal">Purpose</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="text-zinc-400">
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-zinc-300">Worker pool</td>
            <td class="py-3">Fixed goroutines reading from shared channel</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-zinc-300">Buffered channel</td>
            <td class="py-3">Decouples HTTP handlers from processing</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-zinc-300"><code class="font-mono text-cyan-400">select</code> statement</td>
            <td class="py-3">Multiplexes events, timers, and shutdown signals</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-zinc-300">Non-blocking send</td>
            <td class="py-3">Returns false instead of blocking when buffer full</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-zinc-300"><code class="font-mono text-cyan-400">sync.Mutex</code></td>
            <td class="py-3">Protects shared batch buffer and DLQ</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-zinc-300"><code class="font-mono text-cyan-400">sync.WaitGroup</code></td>
            <td class="py-3">Waits for all workers during shutdown</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-zinc-300"><code class="font-mono text-cyan-400">context.WithCancel</code></td>
            <td class="py-3">Propagates shutdown signal to all components</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-zinc-300">Interface dispatch</td>
            <td class="py-3"><code class="font-mono text-cyan-400">Processor</code> interface allows swappable strategies</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-6">API Endpoints</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <th class="text-left py-3 pr-4 text-zinc-400 font-mono font-normal">Method</th>
            <th class="text-left py-3 pr-4 text-zinc-400 font-mono font-normal">Path</th>
            <th class="text-left py-3 text-zinc-400 font-mono font-normal">Description</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="text-zinc-400">
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-4"><span class="text-emerald-400 font-mono">GET</span></td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-zinc-300">/health</td>
            <td class="py-3">Liveness check</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-4"><span class="text-emerald-400 font-mono">GET</span></td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-zinc-300">/ready</td>
            <td class="py-3">Readiness check (pings MongoDB)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-4"><span class="text-emerald-400 font-mono">GET</span></td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-zinc-300">/metrics</td>
            <td class="py-3">Prometheus metrics endpoint</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-4"><span class="text-amber-400 font-mono">POST</span></td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-zinc-300">/api/v1/events</td>
            <td class="py-3">Submit an event for processing</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4"><span class="text-emerald-400 font-mono">GET</span></td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-zinc-300">/api/v1/events/:id</td>
            <td class="py-3">Retrieve a processed event</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-6">Prometheus Metrics</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <th class="text-left py-3 pr-4 text-zinc-400 font-mono font-normal">Metric</th>
            <th class="text-left py-3 pr-4 text-zinc-400 font-mono font-normal">Type</th>
            <th class="text-left py-3 text-zinc-400 font-mono font-normal">Description</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="text-zinc-400 font-mono text-xs">
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-zinc-300">events_received_total</td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4">Counter</td>
            <td class="py-3">Events received by the API</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-zinc-300">events_processed_total</td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4">Counter</td>
            <td class="py-3">Events successfully processed</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-zinc-300">processing_duration_seconds</td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4">Histogram</td>
            <td class="py-3">Per-event processing time</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-zinc-300">batch_write_duration_seconds</td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4">Histogram</td>
            <td class="py-3">MongoDB bulk write time</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-zinc-300">channel_buffer_usage</td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4">Gauge</td>
            <td class="py-3">Events waiting in channel</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-zinc-300">dlq_size</td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4">Gauge</td>
            <td class="py-3">Events in dead letter queue</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-6">Project Structure</h2>
    <div class="architecture-block">
      <pre><code>├── cmd/server/main.go           # Entry point, signal handling, graceful shutdown
├── internal/
│   ├── config/config.go         # Environment-based configuration
│   ├── server/server.go         # HTTP server, routing, component wiring
│   ├── api/
│   │   ├── handlers.go          # HTTP handlers (create, get, health, ready)
│   │   └── middleware.go        # Request logging, metrics middleware
│   ├── event/
│   │   ├── event.go             # Event struct and request/response types
│   │   ├── validator.go         # Input validation
│   │   └── enricher.go          # Timestamp and metadata enrichment
│   ├── processing/
│   │   ├── processing.go        # Processor interface, LogProcessor, BatchProcessor
│   │   ├── worker.go            # Worker pool (goroutines + channel + WaitGroup)
│   │   └── router.go            # Routes events to processors by type
│   ├── storage/
│   │   ├── mongodb.go           # MongoDB client (connect, insert, find, ping)
│   │   ├── batcher.go           # Batch writer (buffer, flush loop, mutex)
│   │   └── dlq.go               # Dead letter queue for failed writes
│   ├── metrics/metrics.go       # Prometheus counters, histograms, gauges
│   └── logger/logger.go         # Structured JSON logging (Zap)
├── .env
├── go.mod
└── go.sum</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>
</ProjectLayout>
